{"id": "EUVD-2024-51819", "enisaUuid": "de4e63ad-8bc8-3b7e-b989-73896781450a", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nexfat: fix out-of-bounds access of directory entries\n\nIn the case of the directory size is greater than or equal to\nthe cluster size, if start_clu becomes an EOF cluster(an invalid\ncluster) due to file system corruption, then the directory entry\nwhere ei->hint_femp.eidx hint is outside the directory, resulting\nin an out-of-bounds access, which may cause further file system\ncorruption.\n\nThis commit adds a check for start_clu, if it is an invalid cluster,\nthe file or directory will be treated as empty.", "datePublished": "2024-12-24T11:28:47", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:09", "baseScore": 7.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a0120d6463368378539ef928cf067d02372efb8c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3ddd1cb2b458ff6a193bc845f408dfff217db29e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/184fa506e392eb78364d9283c961217ff2c0617b", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53147"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53147"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1f911c97-3610-3ce8-88da-6bd13a9e217e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "305febb1-09d7-3d48-8428-c1e5d1997f03", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "3280a18e-1019-38e8-a748-3a7a256256d0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1acf1a564b6034b5af1e7fb23cb98cb3bb4f6003 <a0120d6463368378539ef928cf067d02372efb8c"}, {"id": "4becfe7d-4bad-3240-b3f4-52d3558599c6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.7"}, {"id": "70ac0189-8344-3c81-90a0-4e777cad5329", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1acf1a564b6034b5af1e7fb23cb98cb3bb4f6003 <184fa506e392eb78364d9283c961217ff2c0617b"}, {"id": "a9498c1a-ddb5-35e1-a05a-0c92989e6173", "product